gies\", \"predefined_strategies.json\")\n./forge/utility_scripts/strategy_loader.py:39:    \"\"\"Return all predefined strategy names.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/strategy_loader.py:40:    return [strategy.get(\"name\") for strategy in load_predefined_strategies() if strategy.get(\"name\")]\n./forge/utility_scripts/strategy_loader.py:44:    \"\"\"Load a strategy configuration from the predefined_strategies.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/strategy_loader.py:45:    for strategy in load_predefined_strategies():\n./forge/utility_scripts/strategy_loader.py:53:    strategies = load_predefined_strategies()\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:29:│  └─ predefined_strategies.json   # Named agent + workflow + prompts bundles\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:182:A predefined strategy names the agent it requires; the entry script\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:188:> class contract, per-strategy loop semantics, predefined-strategy bundles,\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:212:intervention named in each predefined strategy's\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:237:| `strategy_loader` | Load named entries from `predefined_strategies.json` and substitute prompt template variables. |\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:264:- **[strategies/predefined_strategies.json](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json)**\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:301:    Entry->>Strat: Instantiate from predefined_strategies.json\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:330:  `@Agent.register(\"name\")`, reference it in a `predefined_strategies.json`\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:337:- **Add a predefined strategy**: append an entry to\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:338:  `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` referencing existing agent +\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:50:| **Predefined strategy** | Named, fully parameterized combination of agent + workflow strategy + prompts + parameters in [strategies/predefined_strategies.json](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json). Selected via `--strategy-name`. |\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:51:| **Post-generation intervention** | Recovery step a strategy invokes when the post-iteration `./gradlew test` still fails. Pluggable via the `PostGenerationIntervention` registry. Configured per predefined strategy (`post-generation-intervention.name`). Concrete implementations: `noop`, `codex_then_pi` (default), `native_trace_collect`. See [workflow-strategies.md §5](workflow-strategies.md#5-post-generation-interventions). |\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:73:- `--strategy-name <name>` — selects an entry from `predefined_strategies.json`.\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:81:Each entry in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` must provide:\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:7:> their predefined-strategy entry; this document defines the underlying\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:62:in their predefined-strategy entry; nothing else changes inside the\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:393:`native_trace_collect` in their `predefined_strategies.json` entry. The\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:10:[`predefined_strategies.json`](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json)) and\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:37:        Predef[(\"predefined_strategies.json<br/>agent + model + prompts + params\")]\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:105:  `__init__` raises if the strategy config from `predefined_strategies.json`\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:226:[`predefined_strategies.json`](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json)\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:250:predefined-strategy entry; today's behaviour is preserved by defaulting to\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:276:Selection in `predefined_strategies.json`:\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:353:   [`strategies/predefined_strategies.json`](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json)\n./forge/README.md:77:Strategies are declared in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Prompt text\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:28:STRATEGIES_PATH = Path(os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, \"strategies\", \"predefined_strategies.json\"))\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:39:        description=\"Run a benchmark suite of libraries using a predefined strategy and aggregate results.\",\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:77:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:122:- `--strategy-name NAME` select a predefined workflow strategy from `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Defaults to `basic_iterative_pi_gpt-5.4` (Pi agent).\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:224:- Run `ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py` for a predefined set of libraries.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:232:  - `strategy`: strategy name matching an entry in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:268:Agents are registered via `Agent.register(...)` and selected per-strategy through the `agent` field in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Supported agents:\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:325:    python3 utility_scripts/schema_validator.py strategy strategies/predefined_strategies.json\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:342:The project uses registry-based workflow and agent abstractions. Each workflow strategy is a Python class that inherits from `WorkflowStrategy` and is registered via a decorator. Agents are registered in the same way via `Agent.register(...)`. Strategies are configured through `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`, which defines the workflow, agent, model, optional provider, prompts, and parameters for each strategy.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:348:If you want to run an existing workflow with a different model or tuned parameters, add a new entry to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Reuse the same `workflow` and `agent` as the base strategy, and differentiate by appending a space and a descriptor to the name:\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:381:1. **Add a strategy entry** to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` with the matching workflow, agent, prompts, and parameters.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:415:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:419:Multiple predefined strategies exist in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`, each using a different source-context combination:\n./forge/AGENTS.md:35:- If the change only alters wording or agent instructions, prefer `prompt_templates/` or `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` over Python logic.\n./forge/AGENTS.md:45:- `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`: declarative workflow configuration such as strategy names, prompt files, parameters, model, and agent selection.\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:129:            \"Strategy name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json \"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:166:            raise ValueError(f\"Fallback strategy '{FALLBACK_STRATEGY_NAME}' not found in predefined strategies\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:78:            raise ValueError(f\"Fallback strategy '{FALLBACK_STRATEGY_NAME}' not found in predefined strategies\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:135:        help=\"select strategy by name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:99:        help=f\"Strategy name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json (default: {DEFAULT_STRATEGY_NAME})\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:79:        help=\"Strategy name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json\",\n./tests/src/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.5.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/hazelcast-validation-test-metadata/serialization-config.json:7:  \"lambdaCapturingTypes\": []\n./tests/src/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.2.1/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/hazelcast-validation-test-metadata/serialization-config.json:7:  \"lambdaCapturingTypes\": []\n./tests/src/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-sdk-common/1.19.0/src/test/java/io_opentelemetry/opentelemetry_sdk_common/Opentelemetry_sdk_commonTest.java:82:    void predefinedCompletableResultCodesAreAlreadyCompleted() {\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
